    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Execution, Not Murder</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard Spencer letter replies to June 1 letter likening Wendy's massacre in Flushing, Queens, to the possible execution of its perpetrators</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A June 1 letter equates the possibility of a state-sanctioned execution of those responsible for the Wendy's massacre to the tragedy of the murders themselves. Fortunately, however, most Americans are still capable of recognizing the vast moral distinction between the supreme punishment, by execution, of a cold-blooded killer, and the supreme brutality of unprovoked murder.</p>
        <p>RICHARD SPENCER  Baltimore, June 3, 2000</p>
      </block>
